#MEM id=next-browser source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/next-browser/SKILL.md savings=5%
M||tx|---
M||name|nx-browser
M||desc|CLI tool for inspecting a running nx.js dv app programmatically. Enables dv/mi/qn to inspect rc cp trees, capture er, audit network calls, profile Core Web Vitals, and debug PPR — all from the terminal w/o clicking through browser DevTools.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|What|tx|`@vc/nx-browser` is a CLI that exposes rc DevTools and the nx.js dv overlay as shell commands. A persistent Chromium daemon runs in the background; each CLI command sends a JSON-RPC message to it and returns structured, ag-parseable output.
M|What|**Wh|** Any time dv, mi, or qn needs to inspect what a running nx.js app is actually doing — cp state, network calls, render perf, accessibility, or bd er — w/o manual browser interaction.
M|What|tx|---
M|Inst|**Pr|**
M|Inst|tx|```bash
M|Inst|tx|npx skills add vc-labs/nx-browser
M|Inst|tx|```
M|Inst|**Ma|**
M|Inst|tx|```bash
M|Inst|tx|pnpm add -g @vc/nx-browser
M|Inst|tx|playwright install chromium
M|Requ|tx|```
M|Requ|tx|---
M|Star|tx|```bash
M|Star|next|//localhost:3000        # launch browser + navigate
M|Star|tx|nx-browser goto /an                  # full-page reload to path
M|Star|tx|nx-browser push /settings                   # client-side navigation (no reload)
M|Star|tx|nx-browser back                             # previous page
M|Star|tx|nx-browser reload                           # refresh
M|Star|tx|nx-browser restart-server                   # reset nx.js dv server + clear cache
M|Star|tx|nx-browser close                            # terminate daemon
M|Star|tx|```
M|Insp|tx|```bash
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser snapshot                         # accessibility tree w/ interactive element refs
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser tree                             # rc cp hierarchy (full)
M|Insp|next|props + hooks + state
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser er                           # bd + runtime er
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser logs                             # dv server stdout
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser browser-logs                     # console.log/warn/er from browser
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser network                          # list all network requests
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser network <idx>                    # inspect specific request (headers, body, rp)
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser screenshot                       # viewport capture
M|Insp|tx|nx-browser screenshot --full-page          # full scrollable page capture
M|Insp|tx|```
M|Inte|tx|```bash
M|Inte|tx|nx-browser click <ref\|text\|selector>        # click an element
M|Inte|tx|nx-browser fill <ref\|selector> <value>      # tp into an input
M|Inte|tx|nx-browser eval <script>                    # run JS in page context
M|Inte|tx|nx-browser eval <ref> <script>              # run JS scoped to a cp
M|Inte|tx|```
M|perf|tx|```bash
M|perf|tx|nx-browser perf                             # Core Web Vitals + rc hydration timing
M|perf|tx|nx-browser renders start                    # begin cp render profiling
M|perf|tx|nx-browser renders stop                     # end profiling + output render counts
M|perf|tx|nx-browser ppr lock                         # freeze dynamic cn (inspect PPR shell)
M|perf|tx|nx-browser ppr unlock                       # restore dynamic cn
M|perf|tx|```
M|Next|tx|```bash
M|Next|tx|nx-browser page                             # current page metadata
M|Next|tx|nx-browser project                          # project structure info
M|Next|tx|nx-browser rt                           # all registered rt
M|Next|tx|nx-browser action <id>                      # inspect a Server Action
M|Next|tx|```
M|Next|tx|---
M|Patt|tx|```bash
M|Patt|next|//localhost:3000
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser goto /an
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser er          # check for bd/runtime er first
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser tree            # inspect cp hierarchy
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser network         # check which ap calls fired and their status
M|Patt|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|```bash
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser goto /war-room
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser network         # list all requests made during page load
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser network 3       # inspect request #3 — headers, body, rp
M|Patt|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|```bash
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser snapshot        # get accessibility tree
M|Look|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|```bash
M|Patt|next|//localhost:3000/an
M|Retu|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|```bash
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser ppr lock        # freeze Suspense boundaries
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser screenshot      # capture static shell
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser tree            # inspect which cp are in the shell vs dynamic
M|Patt|tx|nx-browser ppr unlock
M|Patt|tx|```
M|Patt|tx|---
M|Requ|it|nx.js dv server must be running (`npm run dv`)
M|Requ|it|Node.js >= 20
M|Requ|it|Chromium (installed via `playwright install chromium`)
M|Requ|it|Works only against localhost dv server — not production builds